text: Diborane is a chemical compound made from boron and hydrogen. It has the chemical formula . It has an unusual chemical structure that led to the discovery of three-center two-electron bonds by Christopher Longuet-Higgins. This theory was expanded by William Lipscomb, who used it to improve theories of chemical bonds in general, eventually winning the 1976 Nobel Prize in Chemistry. == References == Category:Boron compounds Category:Hydrogen compounds
